quran[10]{c,v,t,f}:
  30,51,"But if We send a [harmful] wind and they see [their crops] turning yellow, they become ungrateful thereafter<sup>21</sup>.","[21] i.e., they become ungrateful to the previous favors of Allah."
  30,52,"You cannot make the dead hear, nor can you make the deaf hear the call when they turn their backs and walk away.",""
  30,53,"Nor can you guide the blind out of their misguidance. You cannot make anyone hear except those who believe in Our verses, for they are ready to submit [to Allah].",""
  30,54,"It is Allah Who created you in a state of weakness, then after weakness He gave you strength, then after strength He made you weak and old. He creates what He wills, and He is the All-Knowing, the Most Capable.",""
  30,55,"On the Day when the Hour begins, the wicked will swear that they had not stayed [in this world] more than an hour. This is how they were deluded [from the truth]<sup>22</sup>.","[22] They used to make similar wrong estimates in the world that there was going to be no resurrection and accountability."
  30,56,"As for those who were given knowledge and faith will say, “You did stay, according to Allah’s decree, until the Day of Resurrection. This is the Day of Resurrection, but you did not know<sup>23</sup>.”","[23] i.e., you did not acknowledge the truth about the afterlife."
  30,57,"On that Day, no excuse will benefit the wrongdoers, nor will they be allowed to make amends.",""
  30,58,"We have presented in this Qur’an every kind of example for mankind. But no matter what sign you bring them, the disbelievers will surely say, “You follow nothing but falsehood.”",""
  30,59,"This is how Allah seals the hearts of those who have no knowledge<sup>24</sup>.","[24] i.e., those who do not want to know the truth; rather, they refuse it."
  30,60,"So be patient, for Allah’s promise is true, and do not let those who have no faith discourage you.",""
